  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baf \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b9f \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Avoid sending children with Covid symptoms to schools - Medical Specialist Deepal Perera",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "In children with symptoms of covid infection, there is a high rate of detection of infection in routine tests.",
        "Therefore, pediatric specialist Deepal Perera said to avoid sending children with symptoms to school.",
        "Children who have been infected with Covid have an increased rate of symptoms including fever, cough, and sore throat.",
        "When children with these symptoms are tested, it can be observed that the rate of detection of covid infections among them has increased.",
        "The point to be pointed out here is that the detection rate of infected people is high even in routine tests. Schools have now resumed. There is a need to continue the school activities.",
        "Therefore, we request parents to refrain from sending children with symptoms of infection to school. The reason is that the current Covid infection is seen in an environment where it can spread very quickly and easily.",
        "It is essential to follow hygiene guidelines in all cases to prevent re-intensification of the spread of Covid.",
        "Maintain social distance and avoid close contact. He said that good quality face shields should be worn in public places including public transport."
      ],
